Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.95,0:00:04.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As times change, difficult\Ncases increase in number!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.23,0:00:06.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A super-creepy bandaged man!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.48,0:00:08.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let him\Ngo after Ran anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.61,0:00:10.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He sees the single truth\Nfor what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.72,0:00:13.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and looks like a kid\Nbut has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.10,0:00:15.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.58,0:01:49.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran and I met Suzuki Sonoko\Nat her mountain villa
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.35,0:01:52.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to view the autumn leaves.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.39,0:01:55.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also there was Sonoko's sister\Nand graduate student, Ayako,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.77,0:02:00.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ayako's old college friend and\Nimport car broker, Ota Masaru,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.78,0:02:03.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the film magazine editor,\NSumiya Hiroki,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.03,0:02:06.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the food company employee,\NTakahashi Ryoichi,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.33,0:02:10.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and scriptwriter Ikeda Chikako,\Nfor a total of eight people.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.79,0:02:14.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The incidents began when\Na creepy man in bandages
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.27,0:02:16.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,tried to kill Ran in the forest!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.42,0:02:22.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That night, after the only\Nbridge out was destroyed,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.93,0:02:26.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ikeda Chikako was caught\Nand killed by the bandaged man!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.91,0:02:31.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then he tried\Nto kill Ran again!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.90,0:02:40.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why? Why is he after Ran?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.95,0:02:50.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Mountain Lodge Bandage\NMan Murder Case (Part 2).
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.70,0:02:53.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.23,0:02:55.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was attacked again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.12,0:02:56.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By that bandaged man?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.17,0:02:58.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently so...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.96,0:03:00.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.00,0:03:00.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.96,0:03:02.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But how did he get in?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.84,0:03:04.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You did lock the window, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.68,0:03:05.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.24,0:03:05.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.80,0:03:06.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.26,0:03:07.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The window's been cut!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.70,0:03:08.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aha!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.89,0:03:10.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He put his hand through to unlock it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.31,0:03:15.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we're on the 2nd floor!\NHow'd he get up here?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.44,0:03:16.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ota! There!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.80,0:03:20.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He must've used that tree\Nto climb onto the veranda!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.48,0:03:22.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is one serious guy...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.32,0:03:23.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then he--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.28,0:03:26.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's odd--\Nit's pouring outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.53,0:03:28.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he snuck in from out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.78,0:03:30.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's safe to assume\Nhe would track mud inside...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.91,0:03:32.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there isn't any at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.03,0:03:34.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.24,0:03:38.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, it's dangerous to be alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.46,0:03:41.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's all wait in the\Ndining room until morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.83,0:03:42.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good call...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.29,0:03:47.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hate piggyback rides!\NThey're so stupid!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.30,0:03:51.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?\NYou sprained your ankle!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.13,0:03:53.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ayako-{\i1}san{\i0}. Isn't that the thing
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.34,0:03:55.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chikako-{\i1}san {\i0}was\Nwearing around her neck?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.14,0:03:58.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, this is Chikako's choker.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.02,0:04:04.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right after you and the others\Nchased after the bandaged man,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.19,0:04:06.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I found it lying\Nby the front door.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.99,0:04:14.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell is the guy thinking?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.57,0:04:17.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Killing Chikako and\Nattacking Ran-{\i1}chan {\i0}twice!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.48,0:04:20.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if he wants to kill us all?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.32,0:04:21.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.69,0:04:22.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't be serious...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.61,0:04:25.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.20,0:04:30.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He carried Chikako-{\i1}san\N{\i0}into the forest afterward,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.83,0:04:33.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so if her choker did fall off,\Nit would've been there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.87,0:04:36.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what was it doing\Nby the front door?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.71,0:04:41.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you use your karate\Nto beat him up when he attacked you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.67,0:04:43.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not like you, Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.22,0:04:47.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't help it; I'm scared\Nof monsters and stuff like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.35,0:04:51.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no need to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.68,0:04:55.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's six of us,\Nand one of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.94,0:04:58.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt he's dumb\Nenough to attack six--
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.37,0:05:01.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ota-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.15,0:05:02.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.11,0:05:03.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.61,0:05:04.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.61,0:05:05.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell was that for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.41,0:05:08.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's seven people here, not six!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.91,0:05:11.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're just a kid;\Nyou don't count!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.74,0:05:13.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.75,0:05:18.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He protected me\Nwhen I was attacked!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.08,0:05:18.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.50,0:05:22.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.09,0:05:28.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Ran. Did you get\Na look at the guy's face?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.26,0:05:28.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.97,0:05:31.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know his build, though!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.64,0:05:34.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't see his face since\Nit was wrapped in bandages,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.52,0:05:38.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I know his figure because\Nof when I jumped onto him...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.94,0:05:45.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His chest was about this big,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.01,0:05:48.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so he wasn't especially skinny or fat...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.45,0:05:52.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like we can believe\Nwhat some kid says.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.54,0:05:58.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sumiya-{\i1}san{\i0}'s video camera!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.04,0:06:02.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm pretty sure he was recording\Nwhen the bandaged man
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.84,0:06:04.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ran off with Chikako-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.97,0:06:09.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There he is!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.93,0:06:13.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just as I thought,\Nshe has the choker on!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.18,0:06:17.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means that her body,\Nwhich the bandaged man
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.10,0:06:19.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was holding when they\Npassed by the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.73,0:06:23.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,somehow went through this lodge.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.86,0:06:27.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone inside this lodge\Ncould have carried her
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.95,0:06:30.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,through the house\Nand out into the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.45,0:06:36.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But everyone was in this room\Nwhen she was taken!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.08,0:06:43.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shall I make us some coffee?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.79,0:06:45.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.05,0:06:49.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say. You were the last one\Nto see Chikako-{\i1}san{\i0}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.63,0:06:51.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.39,0:06:54.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did she seem out of\Nthe ordinary at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.22,0:06:58.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.39,0:07:01.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she read a note that had been\Nslipped beneath her door...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.27,0:07:04.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She suddenly turned very pale...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.73,0:07:09.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, so she was drawn\Noutside by that note!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.49,0:07:12.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why her slippers\Nwere by the back door--
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.70,0:07:14.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that's where she snuck out from...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.33,0:07:19.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And only someone on the inside\Ncould have put the note there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.54,0:07:23.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean the killer\Nis in this room?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.84,0:07:27.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why did he try\Nto kill Ran twice?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.59,0:07:32.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know his motive\Nfor killing Chikako-{\i1}san{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.89,0:07:35.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but why Ran, who came here\Nat a moment's notice?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.85,0:07:39.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute! What if she had--
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.60,0:07:45.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry! My mistake!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.07,0:07:47.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Ran-neechan.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.65,0:07:48.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.40,0:07:50.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When we got here,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.03,0:07:52.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you opened everyone's door\Nby accident, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.66,0:07:53.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.44,0:07:55.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you see anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.07,0:07:56.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like what?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.45,0:07:58.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like a cape or bandages?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.33,0:08:00.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me\Nthis kid suspects us?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.00,0:08:05.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't pay attention to him;\Nhe just loves playing detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.42,0:08:07.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You really didn't see anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.63,0:08:09.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't see anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.00,0:08:11.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were all changing clothes\Nso I shut the doors right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.42,0:08:15.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I think about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.80,0:08:18.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,something's been\Nbugging me ever since...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.26,0:08:21.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think it was important,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.48,0:08:23.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I can't remember what it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.19,0:08:25.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Try to remember, Ran-neechan!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.82,0:08:29.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The power's out!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.82,0:08:31.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The lightning knocked out a power line!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.49,0:08:34.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm scared!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.07,0:08:35.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get candles from the kitchen!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.70,0:08:38.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You gonna be alright by yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.70,0:08:39.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll come with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.80,0:08:40.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me too!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.58,0:08:45.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This should help\Nfor a little while...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.09,0:08:50.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.58,0:08:52.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It came from the dining room.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.72,0:08:55.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be the bandaged man again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.18,0:09:04.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.39,0:09:06.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was mean, Ran-neechan!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.06,0:09:07.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.06,0:09:08.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's--
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.56,0:09:12.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that an axe?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.74,0:09:14.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that person just now was--
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.20,0:09:18.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The bandaged man is after Ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.07,0:09:20.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why her?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.30,0:09:24.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That sounded like Sonoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.93,0:09:26.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran-neechan! Come on! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.26,0:09:32.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The upstairs window is broken!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.52,0:09:34.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran-neechan!\NGo up to the window!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.81,0:09:37.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ayako-{\i1}san{\i0}!\NCould you hold these?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.57,0:09:41.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at this mess!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.40,0:09:43.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The floor's covered\Nin broken glass!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.94,0:09:48.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The bandaged man must've\Nbroken through this window...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.71,0:09:50.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, he didn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.62,0:09:52.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One of the locks is undone!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.37,0:10:00.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he really did break in\Nthrough this window...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.28,0:10:04.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...then it should still be locked!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.26,0:10:07.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's not!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.21,0:10:10.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Most likely, he unlocked it\Nfrom the inside,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.35,0:10:12.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,stepped onto the veranda,\Nclosed the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.68,0:10:16.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then smashed it to make it\Nlook like he broke in from outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.85,0:10:21.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He snuck in from\Nthe 2nd floor again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.02,0:10:25.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, he probably jumped\Nonto the veranda from that tree...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.02,0:10:26.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No doubt about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.65,0:10:28.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The maniac who killed Chikako-{\i1}san{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.36,0:10:30.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and attacked Ran three times\Nis in this very room!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.29,0:10:36.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are those grooves?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.29,0:10:40.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! Now I understand!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.88,0:10:42.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was a trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.80,0:10:47.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Ran-neechan!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.13,0:10:51.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why is the bandaged man\Nintent on killing Ran?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.68,0:10:55.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What exactly did she see?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.18,0:10:57.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't see anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.89,0:11:00.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were all changing clothes\Nso I shut the doors right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.40,0:11:02.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if he's actually--
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.77,0:11:07.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So the bandaged man really is him!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.61,0:11:08.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If so, then the three mysteries--
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.85,0:11:11.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the reason why the bandaged\Nman passed by the window
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.99,0:11:13.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with Chikako-{\i1}san\N{\i0}for everyone to see,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.74,0:11:17.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,how he was able to carry the body\Ninto the forest unnoticed,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.21,0:11:19.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the reason he's after Ran--
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.50,0:11:22.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they all fit!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.33,0:11:22.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.54,0:11:25.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran's the only detective\NI can use here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.30,0:11:29.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, where are the candles\NI gave you earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.84,0:11:32.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I missed!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.73,0:11:38.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sonoko?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.60,0:11:40.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Sonoko?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.02,0:11:44.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn! I have no choice\Nbut to use Sonoko now!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.11,0:11:46.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sonoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.36,0:11:49.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just figured it out...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.28,0:11:53.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know who killed Chikako-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.42,0:12:02.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just figured it out...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.80,0:12:05.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know who killed Chikako-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.67,0:12:08.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What're you talking about,\NSonoko-{\i1}chan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.76,0:12:11.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer's obviously\Nthat bandaged guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.89,0:12:14.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. He's probably\Nin the forest right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.43,0:12:16.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,just waiting to get us!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.69,0:12:19.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really think there's\Nsuch a person in the forest?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.94,0:12:26.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Think back to the state of Ran's\Nroom when she was attacked...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.99,0:12:30.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He broke in through the veranda, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.74,0:12:35.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. He jumped onto the\Nupstairs veranda from a tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.37,0:12:39.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why were there no\Nmud tracks in Ran's room?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.37,0:12:43.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was raining outside\Nwhen the bandaged man snuck in.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.50,0:12:45.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.55,0:12:47.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason is simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.38,0:12:50.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was because the bandaged\Nman was inside the lodge!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.97,0:12:56.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The point of entry was most likely\NChikako-{\i1}san{\i0}'s room, right next to Ran's.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.18,0:13:00.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer exited onto the veranda,\Nentered Ran's room, and attacked her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.15,0:13:02.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But then she screamed...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.53,0:13:08.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and he hastily ran\Nback to Chikako-{\i1}san{\i0}'s room!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.95,0:13:12.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He quickly changed his clothes
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.45,0:13:18.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and met everyone in Ran's room\Nwith feigned unawareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.37,0:13:23.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the maniac who\Nkilled Chikako-{\i1}san {\i0}and attacked Ran
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.46,0:13:25.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is in this very room!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.59,0:13:29.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sonoko-{\i1}chan{\i0}. Playing\Ndetective is nice and all,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.70,0:13:31.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but think clearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.30,0:13:33.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When the bandaged dude\Nran past the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.47,0:13:37.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,every one of us\Nwas inside the lodge!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.52,0:13:43.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,None of us could possibly be him!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.17,0:13:47.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if you used a dummy\Nand some piano wire,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.11,0:13:50.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it'd be possible to make it\Nseem that way from inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.49,0:13:51.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A dummy?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.60,0:13:56.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. An inflatable one, most likely.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.54,0:14:00.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He affixed Chikako-{\i1}san{\i0}'s\Nbody to the dummy,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.04,0:14:03.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and attached two piano wires\Nto the dummy's head.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.00,0:14:08.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He passed one wire through\Nthe central veranda's railing,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.71,0:14:14.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,tied both ends of the wires to the\Nrailing above the window in question,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.05,0:14:17.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then cut the wire\Nthat went through the railing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.10,0:14:23.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After he swung it\Npast the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.85,0:14:27.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he quickly recovered\Nthe dummy and Chikako-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.23,0:14:29.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chikako!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.44,0:14:32.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only one who\Ncould've pulled that off
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.11,0:14:35.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was the person on the veranda,\Nfixing the roof...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.45,0:14:38.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...you, Takahashi-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.99,0:14:42.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're kidding, right,\NSonoko-{\i1}chan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.90,0:14:47.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The two distinct piano wire\Nmarks on the outside railing...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.38,0:14:49.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...are proof!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.21,0:14:52.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only the stage manager\Nfor your old filmmaking club
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.63,0:14:56.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,could've set up\Nsomething so elaborate!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.18,0:14:59.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't be serious...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.52,0:15:03.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what did I do with\Nthe body after I pulled it up?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.44,0:15:09.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right after that, we all\Nchased him into the forest,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.69,0:15:12.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,where we found\NChikako's body in pieces.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.11,0:15:17.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you see me carrying any bodies?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.45,0:15:18.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.20,0:15:20.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is proof\Nthat you carried her.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.08,0:15:25.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My sister found Chikako-{\i1}san{\i0}'s\Nchoker by the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.08,0:15:29.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was wearing that choker\Nwhen she was abducted.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.75,0:15:33.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The fact that it was by the\Nfront door after everyone left
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.42,0:15:38.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,means that someone went through\Nthe door, carrying her body!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.76,0:15:42.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I already told you,\NI wasn't carrying anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.60,0:15:46.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, nobody could carry\Nthe body without being noticed...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.10,0:15:49.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Assuming it was the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.06,0:15:51.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if it were just the head...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.15,0:15:53.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...it would be entirely possible to carry!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.03,0:15:55.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.40,0:15:59.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, all that we\Nsaw outside the window
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.12,0:16:01.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was her head surrounded by a cape!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.91,0:16:05.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her body had been\Ntorn apart when we found it...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.00,0:16:08.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.09,0:16:12.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would I want to\Nkill her and Ran-{\i1}chan{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.80,0:16:16.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And besides--
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.01,0:16:18.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And besides what?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.05,0:16:21.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why won't you say it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.76,0:16:24.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't there proof?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.18,0:16:29.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You and the bandaged man\Nhave completely different figures...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.11,0:16:33.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, Takahashi-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.53,0:16:35.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The bandaged man isn't fat!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.86,0:16:38.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Takahashi!\NWhy didn't you say so?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.66,0:16:43.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was afraid of what\NI would ask in response:
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.70,0:16:46.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Are you really, truly fat?"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.37,0:16:51.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.\NHe's not fat at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.59,0:16:55.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He stuffed the head in his\Nshirt and carried it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.09,0:17:00.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, he lured Chikako-{\i1}san\N{\i0}into the forest, ripped her apart,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.76,0:17:04.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,replaced the padding under\Nhis shirt with her head,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.35,0:17:06.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and carried it back to the lodge.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.39,0:17:09.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, after doing\Nthe trick on the veranda,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.90,0:17:12.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he stuffed the deflated dummy\Nand head under his shirt
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.36,0:17:15.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and headed for the forest\Nwith everyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.07,0:17:18.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then he dumped\Nthe head in the forest
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.32,0:17:20.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,while pretending to look for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.95,0:17:25.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, this was\Na daring and clever trick
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.24,0:17:31.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in which he faked his figure\Nto freely move the corpse around!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.13,0:17:36.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By using this trick,\Nhe was able to make it look like
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.67,0:17:40.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the bandaged man took Chikako-{\i1}san\N{\i0}into the forest and killed her,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.49,0:17:45.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and that he was responsible\Nfor everything that happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.97,0:17:49.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But his supposedly-perfect plan
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.44,0:17:53.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,began to mess up\Nwhen Ran did something...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.69,0:17:57.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. When she accidentally\Nopened his door,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.53,0:17:59.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she saw it...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.03,0:18:04.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...his real figure!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.16,0:18:08.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She hadn't thought\Nmuch of it at the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.12,0:18:13.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but if she did remember,\Nhis carefully-planned murder plot
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.25,0:18:14.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,would go up in smoke!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.67,0:18:18.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why he attacked\Nher in the forest--
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.97,0:18:20.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to keep her quiet!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.58,0:18:24.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But he failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.47,0:18:27.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Worried that Chikako-{\i1}san\N{\i0}would go down the mountain
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.98,0:18:30.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,during all the commotion,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.69,0:18:34.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he cut the phone line,\Ndestroyed the bridge,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.48,0:18:37.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and shut everyone up inside the lodge!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.40,0:18:42.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He lured Chikako-{\i1}san\N{\i0}into the forest as planned
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.11,0:18:44.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then murdered her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.41,0:18:46.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was lured out by the note
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.04,0:18:49.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that he most likely\Nslipped under her door.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.83,0:18:55.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was probably about\Nfellow club member Atsuko-{\i1}san{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.50,0:18:58.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who committed suicide\Ntwo years ago--
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.20,0:19:01.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true!\NI did it all for Atsuko!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.34,0:19:02.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-Takahashi...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.18,0:19:08.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She secretly showed me\Na story she had written,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.97,0:19:12.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and her eyes sparkled as she told\Nme her dream of being a novelist.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.73,0:19:16.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, one day, she hanged\Nherself in our meeting room!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.41,0:19:20.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once I saw Chikako's\Nlatest movie, "Blue Kingdom,"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.18,0:19:23.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I suddenly knew why she did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.60,0:19:25.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Blue Kingdom"?\
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.35,0:19:26.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me she-
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.97,0:19:29.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. The story\Nfor Chikako's debut work
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.98,0:19:35.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was exactly the same as the "Azure\NCountry" story that Atsuko showed me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.36,0:19:37.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean Chikako...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.69,0:19:38.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...stole it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.82,0:19:41.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. The story won Chikako\Na new scriptwriter's award
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.24,0:19:46.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,while she was still in school,\Nand now she's famous!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.79,0:19:50.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But how do we know\Nthat led to Atsuko's suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.25,0:19:53.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The day Chikako won the award--\Nthe day before Atsuko died--
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.58,0:19:55.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Atsuko told me over the phone
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.13,0:19:59.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that she couldn't trust\Nanyone anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.67,0:20:04.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I lured Chikako into\Nthe forest with a blackmail note
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.18,0:20:07.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then I chopped her head off!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.93,0:20:10.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what she gets\Nfor crushing Atsuko's dream!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.85,0:20:15.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all over now...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.82,0:20:19.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's time for me to see Atsuko...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.53,0:20:21.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on, Takahashi!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.11,0:20:22.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stay away!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.15,0:20:22.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Takahashi-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.32,0:20:26.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to live\Nwith her in the next world
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.16,0:20:28.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as the messenger of\Njustice who avenged her!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.29,0:20:30.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop fooling yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.41,0:20:34.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you wanna die, then die!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.38,0:20:36.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sonoko...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.38,0:20:41.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe you did commit\Na crime for Atsuko's sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.72,0:20:44.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But when you attacked Ran,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.51,0:20:46.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it wasn't for her sake at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.30,0:20:47.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were afraid!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.89,0:20:51.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were afraid of being labeled\Na criminal, so you attacked her!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.68,0:20:53.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're no...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.06,0:20:57.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...messenger of justice!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.27,0:21:00.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're just an ugly,\Nbloodthirsty killer!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.29,0:21:18.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A friend's betrayal\Nled to a friend's death,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.29,0:21:22.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which, in turn,\Ntwisted a friend's heart...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.34,0:21:27.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At long last, the villa breaks\Nfree of the cold and tragic night...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.85,0:21:29.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But beware!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.81,0:21:32.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let your guard down,\Nand he'll appear
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.43,0:21:35.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,from a person's heart again...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.56,0:21:38.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The crazed killer known as "revenge."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.45,0:23:15.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad your\Nsister is doing better now!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.13,0:23:16.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.70,0:23:20.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She stayed in bed for a whole\Nweek after it happened...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.50,0:23:23.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it was all thanks\Nto your great detective skills
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.84,0:23:26.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that the case was solved!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.92,0:23:27.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.17,0:23:29.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.76,0:23:32.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You make a pretty cool\Ndetective, you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.90,0:23:34.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I better change the topic!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.68,0:23:35.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, guess what--
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.89,0:23:40.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, well, cases like that\Nare as easy as pie for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.77,0:23:44.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shinichi-{\i1}kun {\i0}and\Nyour dad are out of luck...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.23,0:23:49.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the great detective\NSuzuki Sonoko's time now!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.70,0:23:57.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Having her be the detective\Nwas definitely a big mistake...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.37,0:24:05.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Yoko has a motive\Nfor killing Nakamoto-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.84,0:24:08.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But she has an airtight alibi!
